HEADWORD: Malevolence
<hw>Ma*lev"o*lence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>malevolentia</ets>. See <er>Malevolent</er>.]</ety> <def>The
quality or state of being malevolent; evil disposition toward another;
inclination to injure others; ill will. See Synonym of
<er>Malice</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
